			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2017</a> paper:</span><br><i>Structural model subtyping with OCL constraints</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ArturBoronat.html">Artur Boronat</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3136014.3136026">10.1145/3136014.3136026</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagM">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a static semantics notion of structural model subtyping constrained by OCL.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It develops formal conditions/definitions for subtyping and constraint satisfaction.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagL">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> Subtyping is motivated by enabling flexible reuse of models and transformations across related model types.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The setting is model-driven engineering where models and constraints form a domain-specific modeling language.
</li></ul></li></ul>
